# TypeScript Component Conventions

## No React.FC — Use Direct Prop Typing

❌ **BAD:**

```typescript
export const Component: React.FC<Props> = ({ prop }) => <div>{prop}</div>;
```

✅ **GOOD:**

```typescript
export const Component = ({ prop }: Props) => <div>{prop}</div>;
```

## Arrow Functions Only

❌ **BAD:**

```typescript
export function Component({ prop }: Props) { return <div>{prop}</div>; }
export default function Page() { return <div />; }
```

✅ **GOOD:**

```typescript
export const Component = ({ prop }: Props) => <div>{prop}</div>;

// Pages/Screens — define then export default
const Page = () => <div />;
export default Page;
```

## Export Patterns

- **Default exports** — Pages (web) / Screens (mobile), entry points (`App.tsx`)
- **Named exports** — Reusable components, hooks, utilities, everything else

```typescript
// Page/Screen — default export
const FeaturePage = () => { /* ... */ };
export default FeaturePage;

// Reusable component — named export
export const FeatureCard = ({ item }: FeatureCardProps) => { /* ... */ };
```

## Explicit Children

Always declare `children` explicitly in props — never rely on implicit children:

```typescript
interface CardProps {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string;
}

export const Card = ({ children, className }: CardProps) => (
  <div className={className}>{children}</div>
);
```

## No Unnecessary Arrow Wrappers

Never wrap a stable function reference in an inline arrow function.

❌ **BAD:**

```typescript
onSubmit={() => handleSubmit()}
onPress={() => onBack()}
onClose={() => closeModal()}
```

✅ **GOOD:**

```typescript
onSubmit={handleSubmit}
onPress={onBack}
onClose={closeModal}

// Exception — when arguments must be passed that the event doesn't supply:
onDelete={() => deleteItem(item.id)}
onPress={() => navigate('Profile')}
```

## Return Types

Let TypeScript infer return types. Only annotate explicitly for:
- Components with complex conditional returns (`JSX.Element | null`)
- Public API / library components
